Bruno Andreas Liljefors (Swedish pronunciation: [ˈbrʉ̟ːnʊ ˌlɪljɛˈfɔʂ] ( listen); 14 May 1860 – 18 December 1939) was a Swedish artist, the most important and probably most influential wildlife painter of the late nineteenth and early twentieth century. He also drew some sequential picture stories, making him one of the early Swedish comic creators. He was brother of the composer and conductor Ruben Liljefors.
